Name: Golden Villa Farmers' Market
Description:
At Golden Villa Farmers' Market, we're all about supporting the local community. Our vendors sell an assortment of quality goods to residents at unbeatable prices.
Previously known as the Asian Farmers' Market, we have been a Stockton staple since 1979. We're open year-round every Saturday. Our hours are 5:00 to 10:00 AM. However, arriving earlier at the market is encouraged as merchants tend to sell out of items quickly.

Name: Running Springs Farmers Market and Artisan Faire
Description: The Running Springs Area Chamber of Commerce Certified Farmers Market and Artisan Faire runs every Saturday, April - the Saturday before Thanksgiving, 9am-1pm. Enjoy a wide variety of Vegetables & Fruit, Microgreens, Honey, Pasteur-Raised Eggs, Fresh Bread, Jam, Coffee, Seafood, Mexican Food, Food Artisans, Sweets, Art, Crafts, Products, Clothing, Body Products, Crystals, Jewelry, Toys, Nonprofit information, and Live Music. Updates are posted on Facebook & Twitter @RSfarmersmarket or Instagram @RS_farmersmarket. The market is nestled between a very nice playground, picnic tables, and the Running Springs Branch Library at 2645 Whispering Pines Drive. At 6,000 feet elevation, the field has nice views of nearby pine trees, blue skies (mostly) and cooler mountain temperatures. The area is considered a Gateway to the San Bernardino Mountains. Many visitors come year-round to enjoy the San Bernardino National Forest.
Address: 2645 Whispering Pines Drive, Running Springs, California 92382
